-- HIGHLIGHTS-Bank of England policymakers discuss June housing measures
-- 
-- Tue Jul 15, 2014 05:13AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, July 15 (Reuters) - Bank of England Governor Mark Carney and three other policymakers appeared before British lawmakers on Tuesday to discuss last month's half-yearly Financial Stability Report, which recommended tighter curbs on mortgage lending.

See below for highlights of the remarks from Carney, Deputy Governor Andrew Bailey and the BoE Financial Policy Committee's external members Don Kohn and Martin Taylor.  CARNEY ON HIGHER LEVERAGE RATIO "The leverage ratio can have effects on, particularly, the business models of building societies and investment banks. Those effects are schematically detailed in the consultation period."